President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their sadness upon hearing of the passing of actress, author, and activist Ruby Dee. They recalled her captivating performances in various roles and how she paved the way for generations of black actors and actresses. They also acknowledged her leadership in the civil rights movement and the doors of opportunity she helped open for all. The Obamas extended their thoughts and prayers to Ruby and her late husband Ossie Davis's three children, friends, and family, as well as to all those who loved them.